# Contract addresses — copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the
# values from your deployment. The shell deploy scripts that used to
# auto-generate this file are no longer in the repo (see
# README.md → "Local / Mock-Oracle Deployment"); paste the addresses
# returned by `wasm instantiate` after each step of the deployment
# sequence.
#
# VITE_FACTORY_ADDRESS:  the factory contract created in deploy step 3
# VITE_ORACLE_ADDRESS:   real Pyth contract on mainnet/testnet, or the
#                        mockoracle instance for local dev
# VITE_POOL_ADDRESSES:   comma-separated list of pool addresses the UI
#                        should surface (anchor + creator pools)
VITE_FACTORY_ADDRESS=osmo1...
VITE_POOL_ADDRESSES=osmo1...
#
# VITE_RPC_ENDPOINT / VITE_REST_ENDPOINT: used by the in-site liquidity
# feature (native GAMM MsgJoinPool/MsgExitPool signing + LP-share supply
# lookup). Point at your target chain — e.g. osmo-test-5:
#   https://rpc.osmotest5.osmosis.zone   /   https://lcd.osmotest5.osmosis.zone
VITE_RPC_ENDPOINT=https://rpc.osmotest5.osmosis.zone
VITE_REST_ENDPOINT=https://lcd.osmotest5.osmosis.zone
#
# VITE_ORACLE_ADDRESS is obsolete post-migration (pricing is x/twap, no
# oracle contract) — left out intentionally.
